Defendant Chelsea K Hoisington in court with attorney Daniel P Fay.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Counts 1 and 2.  Court finds defendant guilty on Counts #1 and #2 of the amended information.  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

COUNT #1:

3 MONTHS JAIL, 

TERM OF PROBATION:  18 MONTHS; (the court would consider early termination of probation after 1 year with agent approval and recommendation);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  

*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling.
*DNA sample/surcharge waived based on date of violation.
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by agent.
*Perform 75 Hours Community Service.  
*Any and all terms deemed appropriate by agent.

RESTITUTION:  $2500.00 (to be paid to Kelly B. to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines);

COURT COSTS:  $253.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

  Expunction is conditionally granted upon verification of completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and no new criminal law violations.



IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

COUNT #2:

60 DAYS JAIL, (CONSECUTIVE TO COUNT #1); 

TERM OF PROBATION:  18 MONTHS;
 (the court would consider early termination of probation after 1 year with agent approval and recommendation);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  

*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling.
*DNA sample/surcharge waived based on date of violation.
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by agent.
*Any and all terms deemed appropriate by agent.

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
